&nbsp;In a colourful celebration of Indian culture, the Consulate General of India, Dr Shashank Vikram and his wife, Dr Megha Singh joined the Durban community for a flag hosting ceremony in Morningside on Tuesday, 15 August.Dancer, Sanyukta Singh performed a dance to commemorate Krishna Janmashtami, also known simply as Janmashtami, an annual Hindu festival that celebrates the birth of Krishna.The flag hosting ceremony is an annual celebration of India&#8217;s independence and this year marks the 70th year of independence. India became an independent nation on August 15, 1947 and Independence Day is a day when people in India and throughout the world pay homage to their leaders and those who fought for India&#8217;s freedom in the past.&nbsp;